create package.json
npm init -y

downdload packages 
npm i express ejs

create app.js 
initialize express 
create /route

add script for npx nodemon app.js as start server

setup ejs
create views folder in root directry
create index.ejs file 
render index.ejs file in app.js

create routes folder in root directory
create user.router.js file 
import the router into app.js
all the routes of the user will be create in user.router.js file 


steps for user registeration
-create 2 /register routes one for "get" and the other one for "post"
-add forntend (used tailwind and flowbite)
-make sure your form tag must have these
 -action="/register"
 -method="post"
 -all the inputs must have name parameter
-add middleware that supports res.body
-add validations using express validator

DB connection
-install mongoose
-create config folder and add db.js file init  abd use mogoose to connect with db 
-create schema into the file user.model.js into models folder  

install: npm i bcrypt


HOW TO USE ENV:
add .env file to the root directory for keeping the secrets
npm i dotenv
setup in app.js






